{
  "stem": "1061.1",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Where you going to be?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Sit here.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So you an listen-- but you have to do it right now because you can't go through later.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You'll be making noise.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, you can't when they-- you make noise.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But it--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My name is Regina Gelb, born Laks.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I also have a nickname.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I go by the name of [?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Rainya ?] as well as Regina.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That is a nickname that derives, really, out of Regina.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was born in central Poland, in Starachowice.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "S-T-A-R-A-C-H-O-W-I-C-E.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It's very difficult to say-- pronounce even worse.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "However, it is known-- it was known, in Poland since the First World War, as a matter of fact, since 1918, because that town became a-- one of the industrial centers of the newborn independent Poland after the First War.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the claim to fame, so to say, for the town was that it had a factory that was basically smelting ore, and producing locomotives and meat grinders and such.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the importance of it all is the fact that when the Second War broke out and the Germans occupied Poland, that factory was immediately converted to war production.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And this became a munitions factory.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And by virtue of that, there was a slave labor camp established in my hometown.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And Jews who were either left in the town after the town was cleared of the Jewish population, or anybody else from surrounding towns who was able-bodied, was shipped into Starachowice, into slave labor camps in which we lived, where there were three shifts operating the factory.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And this was canons for artillery is-- was the basic production during the war.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "All right.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I come from a family of-- of course father, mother, and three sisters.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I am the youngest of the three.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My mother's name was Poline or Pola.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Her maiden name Tenenblum.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "She came from central Poland, [INAUDIBLE] and [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "My father was-- his name was Isaac Laks.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And he came from [INAUDIBLE], which is Western Poland.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And the difference in their backgrounds was that my father was really educated in the German language.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Even though he was a Polish citizen, his basic and higher education was in German.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So my father spoke German fluently.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And he had his encyclopedia in German and his-- his literature was German.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But his Polish, of course, was beautiful.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Mother's on the other hand, was-- had a mixture of the Russian, because as everyone knows from history, Poland was, prior to the First War, divided into three units, Russian, German, and Austrian.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "My mother came from the so-called Russian part.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Anyhow, my father, as I said, came from [INAUDIBLE] in the western part, mother from central Poland from a very large family.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And mother's-- my grandmother, Tenenblum, had 13 children.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "She bore 13 children, nine of whom survived.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And these, of course, like my mother, had their own families.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "So that gives you an idea how large my mother's family was.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And of course, all of them perished.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And well, we lived a very good life.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "We had a very, very kind of a comfortable life.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "My parents-- my mother was very much involved in the Zionist movement.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "She was president of the Women's International Zionist Organization, WIZO, for the district, whether it was the-- I don't know how large the district was, but it probably encompassed number of towns.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "My father was an engineer in the forestry lumber industry.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And both were very well educated.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And the three of us, my oldest sister is Anna, presently Wilson.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "She also had a nickname, [?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "Hanya. ?] The second sister, the middle one, Rosalie [?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "Kristine ?] Lerman, also known as [?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "Krisha. ?] And I am the third one.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And we all attended school.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "We attended Polish schools, not Jewish schools, because our town also had a very sizable Jewish population.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And the religious part of the Jewish population preferred their own schools.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And they had religious schools for girls.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And they had religious schools for boys.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "We did not attend any of those schools.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "We went to the regular Polish school.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And the language spoken at home was Polish.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This was just a public school.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You know, this was just a regular public school in town.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It had no name.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When-- when the war broke out, I was 10 years old.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I never, of course, never finished elementary school before the war.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My oldest sister, Anna, she was already in gymnasium, which is high school, which was a higher level in Poland than it is here.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And my second sister of-- the middle sister, of course, had more education than I.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But my education was cut off right in the middle of-- of elementary school.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
